      <p>  32-year-old Saudi Arabia's Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman, who assumed power one year ago is regarded as a risk-taker and has begun a sweeping campaign of liberalization in the kingdom. Saudi Arabia's transformation is predominantly motivated by the improvement in the economy by allowing more freedom and equality for women.
      <p>   Experts are saying that now that the nation is shifting away from oil reliance and focus more on households that will need dual income.</p> 
